uld account for the 3.1.0 utility-package relocation and existing native-image JRT protocol needs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not add a direct commons-compiler dependency just to fix the compile error: org.codehaus.janino:janino:3.1.0 already declares org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.1.0 transitively. The failing import org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator.Iterables was removed from the janino jar in 3.1.0; if an iterator utility test is still useful, use org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator.Iterables from the transitive commons-compiler jar, or avoid testing that transitive utility when focusing on janino coverage. Preserve/add the existing native-image build setup '--enable-url-protocols=jrt' for tests that exercise Janino compiler/evaluator APIs on JDK 9+ module runtimes. Tests that cook/evaluate/compile Java source should prove JVM behavior but may need to tolerate native-image runtime failures caused by unsupported dynamic class loading.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Testing relocated commons-compiler utilities may shift coverage away from the target janino artifact.\",\n    \"Optional Ant integration exists but is not required for normal Janino usage or meaningful compiler/evaluator coverage; adding org.apache.ant:ant would only be justified if tests deliberately cover AntCompilerAdapter.\",\n    \"Native Image cannot generally load Janino-generated classes at runtime, so tests must distinguish expected native-image limitations from real regressions.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c7a224a47b1cbd2016a426c09595c8196aacdca86f51fce89\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 9572, "output": 1786, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33374, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782737906049, "responseId": "resp_0c7a224a47b1cbd2016